<F P=100> SLOVENIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assembly Passes Budget </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Assembly Passes Budget </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0705165194 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 
1330 GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0705165194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Slovene </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] After a three-day session, the State Chamber 
passed the 1994 budget last night. Some 407.6 billion Slovene 
tolars are expected to accumulate in the state treasury, while 
the budget deficit will reach 12.8 billion Slovene tolars, which 
is 0.8 percent of the estimated GNP. The deficit will thus be a 
good billion higher than anticipated and its increase is 
primarily due to the additional funds for the maintenance of 
local and regional highways. All other allocations of funds more 
or less stayed within the proposed limits. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

