<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Federal </F>
<H3> <TI>   National Renewal Rally Banned </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Renewal Rally Banned </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0705140194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1214 GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0705140194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Belgrade, 7 May (TANJUG) -- Representatives of 
the Serbian National Renewal [SNO] announced at a news 
conference today that the relevant authorities have banned the 
party's convention scheduled for Victory Day on Monday at the 
Republic Square in Belgrade. The SNO said that Vladimir 
Zhirinovskiy, chairman of the Liberal-Democratic Party of 
Russia, was to have addressed the convention. 
  A decree banning the convention, signed by Milos Vukobrat, 
head of the interior affairs department of Belgrade's Stari Grad 
municipality, stresses that the decision was passed because "if 
the meeting goes ahead and there is a breach of public order, 
the safety of people and property will be threatened, and public 
transport will be interrupted." [passage omitted] 
  [Zoran] Atanaskovic [chairman of the SNO executive 
committee] 
said: "We believe that this is a political ban, and the SNO's 
final stance is that the convention will go ahead as planned, 
regardless of whether our appeal to overturn the ban is accepted 
or not." According to him, there have never been any incidents 
at SNO meetings. He added that the party is ready to guarantee 
safety to all participants in the meeting, and that 200 bouncers 
will be provided. 
  Jela Jovanovic, chairman of the SNO's political council, 
confirmed that Zhirinovskiy and his closest aides will arrive 
tomorrow afternoon and spend three days in Belgrade. According 
to her, immediately upon his arrival, Zhirinovskiy will have a 
meeting with republic of Srpska president Radovan Karadzic and 
then hold a news conference in the International Press Center. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

