<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Federal </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ban on Rally Overturned </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ban on Rally Overturned </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0905111394 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1009 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0905111394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Belgrade, 9 May (TANJUG) -- The Serbian Ministry 
of Internal Affairs has given its permission to the Serb 
National Renewal to hold a rally in Belgrade's Republic Square 
later today to mark 9 May -- the day of victory against fascism. 
TANJUG has learned from Milos Vukobrat, head of the internal 
affairs department in the Stari Grad municipality, that this 
morning the Ministry of Internal Affairs accepted the Serb 
National Renewal appeal against the decree banning the rally. 
[passage omitted] According to the SNO, Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, 
the president of the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia, will 
also address a rally scheduled for 1530 today. 

