<H3> <TI>   Granic Meets Velayati </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Granic Meets Velayati </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0705094394 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
0900 GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0705094394 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Croatian delegation headed by Mate Granic, 
deputy prime minister and foreign minister, left for Vienna 
today for the resumption of the talks on the implementation of 
the Washington agreement. The talks at the U.S. Embassy will 
also be attended by the Bosnian Muslim delegation headed by 
Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic and a delegation of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Croats headed by Kresimir Zubak, president of 
the presidential council of the Croat Republic of Herzeg-Bosna. 
Prior to his departure for Vienna, Minister Granic said he 
hoped agreement would be reached on the further implementation 
of the Washington agreement. 
  Before leaving for the talks, Minister Granic met with 
Iranian Foreign Minister 'Ali Akbar Velayati in Zagreb this 
morning. The talks centered on Croatian-Iranian relations and 
the situation in Bosnia-Herzegovina. After a brief visit to 
Zagreb, Minister Velayati will leave for Sarajevo where he will 
meet Bosnia-Herzegovina officials and attend the opening of the 
Iranian Embassy. 

</TEXT>

