<H3> <TI>   RSK `Prepared To Help' Defense of Brcko </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    RSK `Prepared To Help' Defense of Brcko </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0705190694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1805 GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0705190694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Knin, 7 May (TANJUG) -- Discussing the situation 
around Brcko, the Supreme Defense Council of the Republic of 
Serb Krajina [RSK] said in Knin today that the defense of the 
corridor was vital for the Serbian nation west of the Drina 
River. In this context, the council has sent its full support 
to the people and the leadership of the republic of Srpska 
making it clear that the RSK was prepared to help in the 
corridor's defense, as it did when the corridor was established. 
The RSK Supreme Defense Council expressed support for the 
efforts to prevent clashes near Brcko by deploying UN monitors, 
pointing out that the corridor has to remain an integral part of 
the Serb ethnic territory because of its importance, and that 
this was not negotiable. 

</TEXT>

