<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbian Commander on Need To Maintain Corridor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbian Commander on Need To Maintain Corridor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0805113394 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1119 GMT 8 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0805113394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Novi Sad, May 8 (TANJUG) -- Major-General Novica 
Simic, commander of the East Bosnia Corps of the Bosnian Serb 
army, has said that the Serb corridor must not be jeopardized, 
let alone cut, at the Serb town of Brcko because it is the 
lifeblood of the Srpska republic. Bosnian Moslems and Croats 
have been amassing strong forces towards Brcko these days. The 
town of Brcko is located in the narrowest section of the 
corridor which links eastern and western parts of the Srpska 
republic. 
  In an interview to the Novi Sad daily DNEVNIK on Sunday, 
Major-General Simic reiterated that "Brcko is a Serb town and if 
anyone should secure and defend it, it is the Bosnian Serb 
Army," adding that the scenario prepared for Sarajevo and 
Gorazde was not applicable to Brcko. "We hold Brcko, as well as 
the corridor, and there is no price for which we shall allow the 
corridor to fall into Moslem hands," the major-general was 
adamant. 
  It is evident that the Moslem leadership wants a repetition 
of the "Gorazde incident" so that the Moslem Army could break 
through to the River Sava unhindered and cut the corridor with 
the help of the United Nations Protection Force (UNPROFOR) and 
the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), Major-General 
Simic said. Brcko is not Gorazde, he warned, the Bosnian Serb 
Army is preparing to counter any possible attacks. 

</TEXT>

