<H3> <TI>   Croat-Muslim Talks on Federation Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Croat-Muslim Talks on Federation Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0905083894 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0800 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0905083894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The talks with the Croatian delegation on the 
implementation of the constitution of the Federation of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina are continuing in Vienna. Talks are being 
held on the borders, the number of cantons, the distribution of 
the ministries in the government, and the posts in the 
federation. The course of the talks has so far been marked by 
rapprochement in all spheres, but, considering that these are 
very sensitive issues, they will require longer and more patient 
talks. A more specific agreement on the distribution of 
ministries in the government and the posts in the federation is 
expected after the conclusion of the talks on the cantons. 

</TEXT>

