<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Praise Akashi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Praise Akashi </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0705121694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1118 GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0705121694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jagodina, 7 May (TANJUG) -- Momcilo Krajisnik, 
president of the assembly of the republic of Srpska, told Radio 
Jagodina today that Yasushi Akashi, the UN secretary general's 
special envoy, is a man of peace and an esteemed diplomat and 
that it is for this reason that the Muslims consider him 
unsuitable. 
  "All diplomats and soldiers who have been objective and 
unbiased in their quest for peace in these parts have been 
branded as undesirables by the Muslims, who demanded their 
dismissal," Krajisnik said. He stressed: "It is certain that 
the Muslim government is backed and instigated by the United 
States in its demand for Akashi's removal." 
  "To claim that Akashi has sided with the Serbs is an 
abhorrent lie," Krajisnik said. Although he is undoubtedly one 
of those responsible for the bombing of Serb positions around 
Gorazde, in our books he is not among those most responsible. 
That is why we are certainly not in favor of his dismissal, and 
I hope that this will not happen," Krajisnik said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

