<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assets Company Suspends Privatization Deals </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Assets Company Suspends Privatization Deals </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1005105194 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1000 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1005105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The State Assets Management Joint Stock Company 
[AVRT] has stopped the implementation of privatization deals. 
Agnes Papp reports on the background to this decision: 
  [Papp] The AVRT has suspended its sales activities and has 
confined its work until the formation of the new government to 
preparing privatization deals for decisions. This is what AVRT 
Managing Director Lajos Csepi told this program's correspondent. 
He explained his decision by saying that it is clear from the 
result of the first round of the parliamentary elections that 
the composition of the new government will be different from the 
old one and it is conceivable that the new government will 
choose a different privatization strategy, and potential new 
sales could limit this new concept. 
  On being asked why he did not respond to similar requests by 
the large parliamentary parties in the past, Lajos Csepi said 
that he needs government authorization to do it, and the 
government and the minister in charge of privatization have 
still not ordered the AVRT to suspend sales. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

