<H3> <TI>   Japan Resumes Short-Term Credit Guarantees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japan Resumes Short-Term Credit Guarantees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0705132594 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1300 
GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0705132594 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Eijiro Hata, Japanese minister of international 
trade and industry, who met with Deputy Prime Minister Grzegorz 
Kolodko today, announced the resumption of short-term credit 
guarantees for Poland. Minister Hata said that prompt servicing 
of the Polish foreign debt is a condition for the further 
improvement of financial relations with Japan. 
  During the meeting, Deputy Prime Minister Kolodko and 
Minister Hata discussed the latest plans by Japanese firms to 
invest in Poland, the problems of bilateral trade exchange, and 
Japanese technical aid for Poland. 

