<H3> <TI>   UNPROFOR Unable To Locate Missing Serb Tank </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNPROFOR Unable To Locate Missing Serb Tank </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0905113594 Paris AFP in English 1109 GMT 9 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0905113594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, May 9 (AFP) -- UN forces in the Bosnian 
capital have failed to locate a Bosnian Serb tank secreted in a 
Sarajevo suburb since late Friday, UN Protection Force spokesman 
Eric Chaperon said here Monday. UN military observers continued 
to patrol the Grbavica sector, and if the tank was found 
UNPROFOR would go and fetch it, Major Chaperon said. Another UN 
officer noted the Serbs were letting very few military observers 
into the area. 
  The tank, probably a T-34, disappeared late on Friday while 
being transported on a truck from Bosnian Serb headquarters at 
Pale in violation of the 20-ki1ometre (12.5-mile) exclusion zone 
ordered by NATO to bar heavy weaponry around Sarajevo. Chaperon 
reported rising tension at Mostar in the south, and some mortar 
fire at Celic and Visoko in the north-east. He said several 
dozen armed Serb militiamen were still in position on the right 
bank of the river Drina in the Moslem enclave of Gorazde, in 
defiance of an exclusion zone order. 

</TEXT>

