<H3> <TI>   UN Says Bosnian Army Violating Exclusion Zone </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Says Bosnian Army Violating Exclusion Zone </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1005115894 Paris AFP in English 0955 GMT 10 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1005115894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, May l0 (AFP) -- The Bosnian Government 
Army has deployed mortars and anti-aircraft guns near Sarajevo 
in violation of the heavy arms exclusion zone around the city, 
UN officials said Tuesday [10 May]. UN Protection Force 
(UNPROFOR) spokesman Eric Chaperon said the Moslem-led forces 
had heavy weapons and many patrols on Mount Igman, to the west 
of the city, facing Bosnian Serb lines within the 20-kilometre 
(12.5-mile) exclusion zone ordered by NATO in February under the 
threat of air strikes. 
  Another UNPROFOR officer, speaking anonymously, said 
helicopter patrols had on Monday counted four mortars and two 
anti-aircraft guns deployed alongside 1,000 Bosnian army troops 
around Mount Igman, a strategic height overlooking the Bosnian 
capital. Chaperon also reported fresh fighting between Bosnian 
troops loyal to President Alija Izetbegovic and soldiers 
following orders of Fikret Abdic, the renegade Moslem leader of 
the northwestern Bosnian pocket of Bihac. 

</TEXT>

