<H3> <TI>   UNHCR Asks Croats To Lift Limits on Convoys </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNHCR Asks Croats To Lift Limits on Convoys </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0905161794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0905161794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The State Committee of Bosnia-Herzegovina for 
Relations with the United Nations warns of a very serious 
problem regarding the passage of humanitarian convoys on the 
road leading from the Dalmatian coast toward central Bosnia and 
Sarajevo. What is involved is the measure taken by the Ministry 
of Traffic and Communications and the (?Roads) Public Enterprise 
of the so-called Croatian republic of Herzeg-Bosna that -- in 
conformity with the conclusion made by the government of the 
so-called Croatian republic of Herzeg-Bosna on 5 April -- limits 
the passage of vehicles of a certain weight along the said road, 
introduces a road toll, and limits the travelling time and speed. 
  These restrictions make it completely impossible for the 
UNHCR and its partners to continue supplying central Bosnia and 
Sarajevo with food and other kinds of aid. According to the 
Information Ministry of Bosnia-Herzegovina, (Karen Kong 
abu-Zaid), head of the UNHCR mission of Bosnia, informed Dr. 
Hasan Muratovic, chairman of the State Committee of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina for Relations with United Nations, about this 
problem and asked him for all available measures to be taken 
with a view to lifting the said restrictions and enabling normal 
supplies. 

</TEXT>

