<H3> <TI>   Abdic `Mercenaries' Attack in Bihac Region </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abdic `Mercenaries' Attack in Bihac Region </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0905213194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2000 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0905213194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mirza Sadikovic] </F>
  [Text] Today, the joint aggressors stepped up their attacks 
on the Bihac region [words indistinct]. As regards their 
furious assaults, the initiative was taken by the members of the 
treacherous Kladusa paramilitaries [Fikret Abdic's forces], who 
in the early hours of this morning started pounding the 
demarcation lines with all their artillery and other weapons. 
There were also very heavy attacks in Cazin's border areas 
[words indistinct]. 
  In addition to this they are trying to infiltrate commando 
groups. The attacks are being spearheaded by gangs of hardened 
criminals and mercenaries who leave devastation in their wake. 
There is a considerable number of casualties, fatalities, and 
seriously wounded people, in the wake of today's murderous 
attacks. Abdic's mercenaries continue to launch artillery 
attacks in other areas. [passage indistinct] 

