<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Melescanu Welcomes Associate Membership in WEU </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Melescanu Welcomes Associate Membership in WEU </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1005100494 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
0400 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1005100494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Romania, together with eight other Central and 
Eastern European countries, yesterday became an associate member 
of the Western European Union [WEU]. In accordance with the new 
statute, which is included in the political document adopted at 
the meeting of the Ministerial Council of the Union that took 
place in Luxembourg, these nine associate members will regularly 
participate in the meetings of the Council, will be able to 
attend meetings of certain working groups of the organization, 
and will have a permanent connection with the central planning 
body of the WEU in Brussels. 
  Similarly, according to reports by our correspondent Andrei 
Barsan, the countries in Central Europe will be able to 
participate in peacekeeping operations or military activities 
initiated by the WEU. 
  Romanian Foreign Minister Teodor Melescanu, who attended the 
meeting together with Romanian Defense Minister Gheorghe Tinca, 
stressed the importance of yesterday's decision, noting that it 
is the first time that an established security structure in 
Western Europe is opening up to other countries as well. 
  Similarly, Melescanu said that for Romania the act of 
becoming an associate member of the WEU -- that is, the armed 
wing of the European Union and at the same time the European 
pillar of NATO -- reflects the steady efforts of the Romanian 
Government to achieve integration into all European structures 
and recognition of the path traveled by our country, as our 
country has recuperated certain arrears in a spectacular way 
compared with other countries in the region as far as 
integration is concerned. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-55082 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu090_c_94001" </HT>


