<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslim-Croatian Talks Continue in Vienna </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslim-Croatian Talks Continue in Vienna </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1005103594 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1005103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Amir Hodzic from Vienna] </F>
  [Text] The talks between the delegations of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and Croatia are continuing in Vienna today on 
the implementation of the Constitution of the Federation of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. Details concerning the borders of the 
Herzegovina cantons are to be worked out today. Last night our 
delegation put forward several proposals as to possible 
solutions, after which the Croatian delegation asked for a break 
in order to conduct additional consultations. Even though these 
are delicate matters, the delegations are expected to complete 
this part of the job today, and then approach the agreement 
concerning the package, which includes the number and borders of 
the cantons, and the distribution of the ministerial positions 
in the government and the functions in the federation. 

</TEXT>

