Daily Report 
<DATE1>  9 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Federal </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia's Zhirinovskiy on Plans To Defeat West </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia's Zhirinovskiy on Plans To Defeat West </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0905172694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1638 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0905172694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 9 May (TANJUG) -- The Serb National 
Renewal Party [SNO] organized a rally in Belgrade's Republic 
Square. Among others the gathering was addressed by Vladimir 
Zhirinovskiy, president of the Liberal Democratic Party of 
Russia [LDPR]. SNO representatives pointed out that the meeting 
was organized to mark the 49th anniversary of the victory 
against fascism and as a harbinger of the upcoming Serbian 
victory. 
  Addressing the rally, Zhirinovskiy said that Russia would 
get 
a new government and a new president soon. "The day after we 
will renew all our relations with Yugoslavia and Serbia, sending 
you all necessary aid, including military aid," Zhirinovskiy 
said. 
  According to him, a new holiday will be marked soon -- "the 
day when the last foreign soldier left the Balkans, the day when 
sanctions against Yugoslavia are suspended." Zhirinovskiy said 
that if representatives of the Serbian nation ask the Russian 
Parliament for aid, "hundreds of thousands of Russian soldiers 
would soon arrive in the Balkans." 
  Expressing his opinion that the conflict in the Balkans 
could 
escalate, Zhirinovskiy said that "If NATO and the Muslim world 
begin a third world war" the Slavs would celebrate 9 May in the 
future "in all Western cities," while all capitals of NATO 
members "would be dealt with in the same way as with Berlin in 
1945." 
  He pointed out that the Russians do not have to fight. "We 
will just let our defective nuclear submarines sail toward the 
West and that will be the end of Western Europe," Zhirinovskiy 
said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

