  [Text] Budapest, 9 May (MTI) -- The Alliance of Free 
Democrats (SZDSZ) is the only force which may counterbalance the 
excessive power of the Hungarian Socialist Party. This will be 
at stake in the second round of the parliamentary elections, 
SZDSZ Chairman Ivan Peto told a news conference tonight. 
  "The Free Democrats are satisfied with their result, namely 
the acquisition of 20 percent of votes in the first round," Peto 
said. In his view, high voter participation is a success of 
Hungarian democracy. As a result, the government to be formed 
will have a great deal of legitimacy. "The SZDSZ has achieved 
its main goal: the government has been dismissed," Peto said. 

