<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 9 May (MTI) -- The Hungarian Democratic 
Forum (MDF) has received fewer votes than expected, and must 
accept the result of the elections, Hungarian Prime Minister and 
MDF Deputy Chairman Peter Boross told a news conference tonight. 
He said he hoped no one would doubt that the Hungarian 
elections were free and democratic. 
  "The Hungarian Socialist Party has made a push forward. The 
vote expressed the will of the people and should be accepted 
