<H3> <TI>   Individual Constituency Totals Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Individual Constituency Totals Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0905122094 Budapest MTI in English 0951 GMT 9 May 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0905122094 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 9 May (MTI) -- After counting 99.9 
percent of the votes, the unofficial computerized report states 
that candidates of the Hungarian Socialist Party (MSZP) lead in 
160 of the 176 individual constituencies, and have already 
secured two parliamentary seats. In addition, MSZP candidates 
finished in second place in 15 of the remaining constituencies 
and in third place in one. In other words, the Socialist 
Party's candidates are in the running for the second round in 
all individual constituencies. 
  Candidates of the Alliance of Free Democrats finished first 
in 12 constituencies, second in 125, and third in 25. 
  The Hungarian Democratic Forum has one candidate who awaits 
the second round in first place, 18 in second, and 81 in third. 
  The Independent Smallholders Party came in second in five 
constituencies, third in 42. 
  The Christian Democratic People's Party won in one 
constituency, was second in seven, and third in 10. 
  The Federation of Young Democrats secured one second place 
and 11 third places in the individual races. 
  The Workers' Party has one second and two third places. 
  The Agrarian Federation has one first and two second places. 
  Independent candidates finished second in one constituency 
and third in two. 
  The Republic Party managed to come in second in one 
constituency. 

</TEXT>

