<F P=101> Poland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Walesa Holds Meeting With UK's Hurd </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Walesa Holds Meeting With UK's Hurd </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0605144594 Warsaw PAP in English 1246 GMT 6 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0605144594 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, May 6 -- President Lech Walesa received on 
Friday British Foreign Secretary Douglas Hurd, who is on a 
working visit to Poland. President said that he is satisfied 
with Polish-British relations and stressed that Poland attaches 
great importance to bilateral relations. He also expressed the 
hope that the Polish point of view on the development of 
situation in eastern Europe would be better understood by Great 
Britain. 
  Douglas Hurd expressed his satisfaction at the meeting 
emphasising that Poland made huge progress on the path of 
transformations under Walesa's leadership. Changes taking place 
in Europe, however, require cooperation, especially in 
political, economical and military areas. Our common aim, said 
the British politician, should be unification of Europe, whose 
Poland is a very important member. 

</TEXT>

