<H3> <TI>   Serbs To Carry Out `Exercises' in Villages </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs To Carry Out `Exercises' in Villages </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0605153594 Tirana ATA in English 1022 GMT 6 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0605153594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, May 5 (ATA) -- Serbian military forces and 
vehicles are being concentrated in the Dubovc village of 
Vushtrise in Kosova. They are expected to engage in a series of 
military exercises which, according to Serbian military 
officials, will continue until May 16 and also extend to the 
villages of Galice and Mikushnice, according to reports from 
Prishtina. 
  The Serbian military command has ordered the stopping of the 
movement of the population between May 9-11 in the said villages 
because of the use of firing arms by the forces during their 
training. 
  Also, on May 4, two columns of the Serbian Army, with many 
armoured vehicles headed for the villages of Duboc, Galice, and 
Mikushnice of Drenice. The Serbian officers ordered the staff 
and pupils of the elementary school Azem Bejtja not to move on 
next Monday, Tuesday, and Wednesday [9, 10, 11 May] from 0400 
o'clock in the morning until 1600, because of the military 
exercises. Other inhabitants of these Albanian villages were 
warned of this, as well. 
  Sources from these villages report that the people's 
movement, especially at night, is very dangerous because of the 
military presence. 

</TEXT>

