BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, May 6 (ATA) -- According to an annual 
report of the International Corporation of Free Trade Unions of 
Kosova, published recently, Serbian authorities have dismissed 
from their jobs 147,000 Albanians who are replaced by Serbians 
and Montenegrins. Besides, there are 125 other Albanian workers 
who are also dismissed by the Serbian administration of the 
Product Enterprise in Skenderaj, which takes the third place for 
its capacity in Kosova. 

