<H3> <TI>   Kukes Strike Continues; Health Issues Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kukes Strike Continues; Health Issues Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1005162494 Tirana ATA in English 0806 GMT 10 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1005162494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, May 10 (ATA) -- The hunger strike staged by 
representatives of the villages over flooded by the lake of the 
Fierza Hydro-Power Station entered in its sixth day. The health 
state of the strikers is getting worse. According to Doctor 
Azem Brasha, many of the strikers are suffering from bronchitis 
and two of them have been hospitalized. The unsuitable hall in 
which the strikers are placed has its own effect on the 
worsening of their health. 
  Meanwhile, in front of the building of the district council, 
where the strike is being staged, crowds of people gather time 
and again in support of the strikers. The chairman of the 
commission of the strike, Jahir Trota, told ATA that the 
strikers are determined to welcome Premier Meksi in Kukes and 
are delighted that the president and the government consider 
their demands as right. 
  In the meantime, the political forces and local government 
keep constant contacts with the strikers in order to find a way 
out to stop the strike and start dialogue regarding their 
demands. The strikers refuse to evacuate the building of the 
district council, an unlawful act, and continue the strike in 
another place because they are afraid the state bodies will 
continue to be indifferent towards them. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

