BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Andrey Sharkov] </F>
  [Excerpt] Sofia, May 5 (BTA) -- [passage omitted] Speaking 
before journalists during a reception at the Austrian Embassy 
here yesterday, Austrian Defense Minister Dr. Fasslabend 
expressed Austria's high appreciation for Bulgaria's 
unquestionable contribution to the stability in the Balkans. 
Mr. Fasslabend stressed the significance the observation of the 
Yugo-embargo has for preventing an expansion of the conflict. 
He conferred on Defence Minister Aleksandrov a high Austrian 
award given for services rendered to Austria. Mr. Aleksandrov, 
the first foreign defence minister to receive this award, was 
decorated for his contribution in promoting the stability in the 
Balkans, Mr. Fasslabend said. The only person entitled to a 
higher award is the Austrian president, Austrian Embassy sources 
told BTA. Bulgarian Chief of General Staff Army General Lyuben 
Petrov and Major General Lyubomir Getchev, too, received awards 
for their contribution to the regional stability and bilateral 
cooperation. [passage omitted] 

