<F P=101> Romania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chamber Ratifies Convention on Human Rights </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chamber Ratifies Convention on Human Rights </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1005162894 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 0847 GMT 10 May 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1005162894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES, 10/5/1994 -- The Romanian 
Chamber of Deputies unanimously adopted, on 9 May, the draft law 
regarding the ratification of the convention on human rights 
defense and fundamental freedoms, as well as its additional 
protocols. By this convention -- adopted on 4 November 1950 and 
signed or ratified by all member states of the Council of Europe 
-- as well as by the ten protocols added subsequently, several 
civil and political rights are guaranteed: the right to freedom 
and security of the individual, the right to an equitable civil 
and criminal trial, freedom of expression, the right to free 
elections and respect of property. 
  The adopted draft provides however under the following 
reserve: "The adoption of the convention shall not prevent 
Romania from putting into application the legal provisions 
through which military discipline is regulated and neither shall 
it impose additional financial obligations related to the 
private education system, others than those set under the 
domestic law". The convention has been previously adopted by 
Romania's Senate. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

