<F P=103> AU1105071694 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, May 10 (CTK) -- Ondrej Hanko, spokesman 
for the shadow cabinet of the Movement for a Democratic Slovakia 
(HZDS) and the Slovak National Party (SNS) described as an 
"extraordinary press conference of victims" a meeting of 
representatives of companies whose privatization projects 
approved in February and March have been canceled. 
  The new Slovak Government of Premier Jozef Moravcik canceled 
on March 29, due to legal and factual shortcomings, 13 of the 45 
privatization projects approved by the government of ex-premier 
and HZDS Chairman Vladimir Meciar at a time when its remaining 
