<H3> <TI>   Ruml Expresses Opposition to KDS Deputy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ruml Expresses Opposition to KDS Deputy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1005164994 Prague LIDOVE NOVINY in Czech 6 May 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> AU1005164994 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague LIDOVE NOVINY </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["(mst)"-signed report: "Ruml Does Not Want a Deputy From </F>
the Christian Democratic Party"] 
  [Excerpt] Prague -- Interior Minister Jan Ruml declared 
yesterday that he does not need another deputy in his ministry. 
He was replying to a question on whether he accepts the demand 
from Christian Democratic Party [KDS] Deputy Chairman Vaclav 
Benda for one of the deputy interior minister's posts for his 
party, a post that -- according to Benda-- should compensate the 
KDS for the fact that his party did not obtain the post of 
attorney general. The interior minister declared that, at the 
moment, he has three deputies from the coalition parties and 
Deputy Minister Fendrych, "whom he needs." According to Jan 
Ruml, he does not need to increase the number of deputy 
ministers merely to satisfy the ambitions of certain people from 
the KDS. 
  Nevertheless, Ruml admitted that the KDS has a claim to this 
post in accordance with the coalition agreements. If, however, 
coalition representatives begin to negotiate on a potential 
deputy interior minister from among the ranks of the KDS, Jan 
Ruml intends to "enter very forcibly" into these negotiations. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

