BFN 

  [Text] Just under an hour ago, President Lech Walesa 
returned to Warsaw from his two-day visit to Estonia. Here is 
what he told newsmen at the airport: 
  [Begin recording] [Unidentified reporter] What is the 
significance of the visit to Estonia? 
  [Walesa] I had to sort out matters in Europe. We have to 
take 
all opinions into account, because we are building democracy, 
after all, and on this road a revisit to Estonia was in order. I 
think that that country indeed has many possibilities, and it 
would be worth doing a bit of business with it. And I think 
that after my visit, some such business will be done. 
  [Reporter] Is cooperation with the Baltic states the 
direction for Poland and the central-eastern European states? 
  [Walesa] Well, it isn't the only direction, but it's 
nevertheless quite an important one. The Scandinavian route -- 
via the Baltics, as they call it -- the whole idea is a very 
good one, and I think Poland should join it as quickly as 
possible. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

