<F P=106> ["D.H."-initialed report: "April Inflation 2.1 Percent"] </F>
  [Text] Ljubljana -- According to a report by the Slovene 
Statistical Institute, retail prices in April have increased by 
2.1 percent, therefore, this is how high the April inflation is. 
In the month just ending, the prices of vital necessities 
increased by 2.4 percent. In the first four months of this 
year, retail prices increased by 6.1 percent and the prices of 
vital necessities by 7.2 percent. In one year, retail prices 
increased by 20.8 percent and the cost of living by 21.8 percent. 

</TEXT>

