<H3> <TI>   Izetbegovic, Gore Discuss Geneva Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Izetbegovic, Gore Discuss Geneva Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1005212194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2000 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1005212194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] U.S. Vice President Al Gore this evening telephoned 
Alija Izetbegovic, president of the Bosnia-Herzegovina 
Presidency, to talk about the upcoming quadripartite meeting in 
Geneva with Bosnia-Herzegovina as the main topic. The second in 
command in the U.S. Administration appealed to President 
Izetbegovic for flexibility to ensure the latest efforts by the 
international community to find a political solution to Bosnia 
are successful. We shall do our utmost to bring about peace 
that will guarantee our people all their rights, Izetbegovic 
told U.S. Vice President Al Gore during this evening's telephone 
conversation. 

</TEXT>

