<H3> <TI>   Government Denies `Secret' Pact </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Denies `Secret' Pact </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1005211194 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1930 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1005211194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1930 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] No secret agreement exists between the current 
government coalition and ethnic Hungarian political groups, nor 
any other document overstepping the framework of the government 
policy statement which was endorsed by parliament, said Lubomir 
Lintner, director of the government's Press and Information 
Office, in an interview with a TA SR correspondent today. 
  Lintner was reacting to the statement of former Prime 
Minister Vladimir Meciar in the "Kroky" television program on 
Sunday in which Meciar said that the current government is a 
vassal of the Hungarian political parties. 

</TEXT>

