<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhelev, Agrarian Union Discuss `Crisis' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhelev, Agrarian Union Discuss `Crisis' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1005160894 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1500 
GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1005160894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 10 May, President Zhelyu Zhelev received a 
delegation of the Permanent Board of the Bulgarian National 
Agrarian Union [BZNS] led by BZNS organizational secretary Petko 
Iliev. The government crisis and the progress of the agrarian 
reform were discussed. The meeting took place at the initiative 
of the Agrarians. After the meeting, Mr. Iliev stated that 
there are no differences between the two sides on the necessity 
of replacing the cabinet and holding early parliamentary 
elections. According to Mr. Iliev, President Zhelev expressed 
skepticism regarding the upcoming changes in Lyuben Berov's 
cabinet. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

