<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Views on Upcoming Assembly Session Examined </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Views on Upcoming Assembly Session Examined </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    BSP Denies Plan To Bring Down Cabinet </H4>

<F P=102> AU1005164694 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1005164694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At a news conference by the Bulgarian Socialist 
Party [BSP] Executive Bureau on 10 May, it was announced that 
the BSP has no intention of toppling the government on 11 May. 
According to the Socialists, it is implausible that the 
structural and personnel changes Prime Minister Berov intends to 
propose would put a question mark over the future existence of 
his cabinet. 

</TEXT>

