<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Flag Altered at Fair; Explanation Demanded </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Flag Altered at Fair; Explanation Demanded </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1005170694 Skopje MIC in English 10 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1005170694 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MIC </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Sun `Trimmed' From Macedonian Flag in </F>
London"] 
  [Text] At the CITEX [expansion unknown] fair in London, 
which is attended by the participants from 25 Central and 
Eastern European countries, the symbol on the Macedonian [FYROM 
-- The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia] flag -- the Sun of 
Vergina -- was printed in the form of a sunflower! However, the 
authentic Macedonian flag is printed on the invitation for 
applications to this fair. 
  The organizers of the Macedonian stand at this fair have 
confirmed that the invitation had the "trimmed" sun from the 
Macedonian flag printed on it, which is seen as a provocation! 
Today, the Macedonian Ambassador in Great Britain Risto 
Nikovski will ask for an official explanation from the CITEX 
organizers. It is unclear as to who made the change of symbols 
on the flag, printed on the invitation for the participation to 
the fair. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

