<H3> <TI>   Berisha Meets Iliescu, Lays Wreath </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berisha Meets Iliescu, Lays Wreath </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1005114194 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1000 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1005114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An official ceremony took place this morning at 
Cotroceni Palace during which President Ion Iliescu welcomed the 
president of the Republic of Albania, Sali Berisha, who is 
making a visit to our country. The talks between the two 
presidents were followed by an official dialogue between the two 
delegations, which include members of the two governments and 
high-level state officials of the two countries. 
  President Sali Berisha attended a wreath-laying ceremony at 
the Monument to the Unknown Soldier before holding a meeting 
with representatives of the Cultural Union of Albanians in 
Romania at the Albanian Embassy in Bucharest. Talks between the 
Albanian president and the president of the Chamber of Deputies 
and visits to the Parliament Palace and the National History 
Museum in Bucharest are scheduled for this afternoon. 
  This evening Iliescu will host an official dinner in honor 
of 
the Albanian president. A treaty of understanding, cooperation, 
and good-neighborliness between Romania and Albania will be 
signed tomorrow at Cotroceni Palace, our correspondents have 
reported. 

</TEXT>

