<H3> <TI>   Berisha Requests Support on CE </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berisha Requests Support on CE </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1005194494 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1800 
GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1005194494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Albanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Telephone report by Shpetim Roqi from Bucharest] </F>
  [Text] President Berisha was received this afternoon at 
the Chamber of Deputies by Chairman Adrian Nastase and Senate 
Vice President Ioan Lup. President Berisha acquainted the 
Romanian parliament representatives with Albania's achievements 
in the field of legislation. There exists greater cooperation 
possibilities with Romania, he said, not only in the field of 
economy and politics but also between our parliaments. 
  President Berisha noted that we are for dialogue between 
Prishtina and Belgrade in the presence of a third party. For 
this, we demand that you insist that Belgrade enter a dialogue. 
President Berisha also requested Romania's support for 
Albania's full membership to the Council of Europe [CE], since 
Albania long ago fulfilled conditions for this membership. 
  For their part, the Romanian representatives said that they 
feel close to Albania and regard cooperation with the Albanian 
parliament highly. They assured President Berisha that they 
will strongly support Albania's full membership in the CE. The 
meetings are to continue this evening and tomorrow morning. 

</TEXT>

