<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karadzic `Cannot Foresee' End to War Soon </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karadzic `Cannot Foresee' End to War Soon </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105162494 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1512 GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1105162494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brcko, 11 May (TANJUG) -- Radovan Karadzic, 
president of the Srpska republic, told journalists in Brcko 
today that he cannot foresee an end to the war in the near 
future, although the Serb people want it. His statement came 
after the 40th session of the Srpska republic people's assembly, 
which adopted conclusions on topical issues of foreign and 
domestic policy. Members of the public were not present at the 
assembly's discussions. 
  "The latest attack by Muslim forces on Brcko rules out any 
possibility of their having any part of Brcko," Karadzic 
stressed. "Brcko has been and will remain a Serb town." 
  The Srpska republic president called on the people in Serb 
Posavina to be vigilant and strong and to remain in this 
territory "to defend it well and be convinced of their own 
victory." "There can be no discussion about the territory, 
which is vital for the Serb people," the Srpska republic 
president said. 
  In his statement for journalists, Karadzic reaffirmed the 
stands contained in the negotiating platform of the Srpska 
republic adopted in March this year, which is still in effect 
and according to which "no negotiations on the former 
Bosnia-Herzegovina can be possible if there is no peace." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

