<H3> <TI>   To Seek Release of French Aid Workers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    To Seek Release of French Aid Workers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1205081594 Paris AFP in English 0759 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1205081594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, May 12 (AFP) -- Bosnian Serb strongman 
Radovan Karadzic, after sharp warnings from Paris, said Thursday 
[12 May] he would find a way to free 11 French aid workers held 
by his troops for the past month for alleged arms smuggling. 
Karadzic was quoted by the Bosnian Serb news agency as saying 
he had decided to "find a legal way" that would allow the 
release of the 11 French nationals employed by the Premiere 
Urgence (First Aid) group who have been held since April 8 in 
the outlying Sarajevo suburb of Lukavica. 
  (In London, European Union negotiator Lord Owen confirmed 
the 
aid workers would be freed "very soon." He told AFP he had 
received this assurance overnight from a trusted intermediary 
who was speaking on Karadzic's behalf. Owen said the Frenchmen 
would be freed "without condition and without trial.") 

</TEXT>

