<F P=102>   AU1105203894 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2000 GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1105203894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At approximately 2000 the Muslims attacked Brcko 
again. Let us listen to what our correspondent Brane Bozic has 
just reported: 
  [Begin Bozic recording] To be precise, the suburbs of this 
town called Grcice were attacked. Several artillery shells, 
most probably of large caliber as their explosion could be heard 
very far away, landed there. The grenades were falling on 
residential homes and in the vicinity of an electrical current 
transformer which supplies this town with electricity. The town 
remained in darkness while the residents rushed into cellars. 
  Ambulance vehicles and the fire brigade sped toward Grcice. 
As of the time of this report, no further details are 
ascertainable. Nobody is on the streets except for the police, 
reporters, and the army. [end recording] 

