<H3> <TI>   Serb Army Preparing Offensive </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serb Army Preparing Offensive </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1205085694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0800 GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1205085694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Hamid Deronjic from Brcko] </F>
  [Text] Last night on the Brcko front was marked by the 
Serb aggressor's provocative fire. The chetniks were firing 
with small arms along the entire front line, while on the 
central part of the front the aggressor also used grenades, 
portable rocket launchers, and Broving. Last night at 1935 from 
the direction of Cadjavac the enemy shelled the defense 
positions in Vranovaca, and at about 2000 the chetnik 
antiaircraft guns and machine guns fiercely pounded Boderiste. 
  Strong chetnik infantry forces are constantly on the move, 
searching for the best positions for offensive activities. Last 
night the enemy sabotage and reconnaissance groups were the most 
active on the central part of the front, facing the positions of 
the 108th Motorized Brigade and the 108th Infantry Brigade in 
the region of Vranovaca and Boderiste. 
  The Serb aggressor is trying to forge an excuse for 
launching 
his long-planned offensive, now that the UN observers are in the 
temporarily occupied Brcko. The chetniks are currently trying 
to do this with their propaganda campaign concerning the alleged 
attacks by the fighters of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army on 
civilian targets in Brcko. However, after the unfortunate 
episodes in Srebrenica, Zepa, Gorazde -- and after the transport 
of the chetnik tanks through the protected zone in Sarajevo, 
when one of the aggressor's tanks mysteriously disappeared -- 
the chetniks simply cannot be trusted with anything. 

</TEXT>

