<H3> <TI>   Karadzic Views Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karadzic Views Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105135794 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1345 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105135794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brcko, May 11 (TANJUG) -- Bosnian Serb President 
Radovan Karadzic said on Wednesday the combined Croat-Moslem 
artillery attack on Serb-controlled Brcko in northeastern Bosnia 
on Tuesday had made the Serbs much more reluctant to make 
concessions in the future territorial delineation. "This once 
again proved us right in insisting that our corridors be 
sufficiently deep from the strategic point of view ... to make 
our borders easy to defend," Karadzic said early on Wednesday 
during a visit to the victims of the attack in Brcko hospital. 
"These civilians have paid dearly for their freedom and the 
right to hold political meetings in their town," he added. 
  During the attack, mounted at 7.30 p.m. local time (5.30 
p.m. 
GMT) on Tuesday, the Bosnian Serb parliament was in session in 
Brcko. 
  A statement issued by the hospital in Brcko said the attack 
left three people dead, including one child and one pregnant 
woman, and 13 others wounded. Bozo Isailovic, 61, his 
daughter-in-law Svetlana, 27, who was in advanced pregnancy, and 
her two-year daughter Bozana were killed at their home which 
sustained a direct hit from a tank shell. Two of the wounded are 
in intensive care, six with severe wounds are undergoing 
hospital treatment and five have been discharged after receiving 
medical help. 
  Karadzic told reporters that Bosnian Serbs had always 
granted 
passage through their territory to Croat and Moslem deputies. 
"Otherwise, their joint parliament would be unable to hold any 
sessions in Sarajevo." Bosnian parliament Speaker Momcilo 
Krajisnik, who visited the wounded together with Karadzic, said 
that what had happened last night in Brcko was the crime against 
the Serb people and an anticivilizational act. 

</TEXT>

