<H3> <TI>   Bulatovic, Kosovo Governors Discuss Security </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bulatovic, Kosovo Governors Discuss Security </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105175094 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1548 GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1105175094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pristina, 11 May (TANJUG) -- Federal Defense 
Minister Pavle Bulatovic and his aides today spoke in Pristina 
with the governors of the Kosovo and Metohija districts and with 
representatives of the military authorities about issues 
relating to the implementation of the policy and system of 
defense in Kosovo and Metohija, the Federal Defense Ministry has 
announced. 
  All issues of relevance to the security system were 
comprehensively discussed. The governors stressed that there is 
very wide-ranging and successful cooperation between state 
authorities and units and command bodies of the Yugoslav Army. 
  Bulatovic said that the political, security, and economic 
situation in Kosovo and Metohija demands the permanent 
involvement of the republican and federal governments. 
  The successful cooperation of civilian authorities and units 
of the Yugoslav Army and organs of the Interior Ministry is of 
extreme importance, because for the time being this is the only 
reliable way of keeping the peace in Kosovo and Metohija, the 
federal defense minister stressed. 
  Minister Bulatovic today observed exercises carried out by 
units and command bodies of the Third Army and some units of the 
Serbian Interior Ministry. 

</TEXT>

