<F P=106> [TA SR report: "The Slovak Republicans Have Changed Their </F>
Name"] 
  [Text] The Republican Bloc-Republican Party (RBRS) is the 
new name adopted on Saturday [7 May] by the participants in the 
Republican Party's Second General Assembly in Bratislava. The 
RBRS acknowledges the principles of neoconservatism and supports 
the rapid realization of economic reform. It is offering to 
cooperate with all right-wing parties in Slovakia. 
Anticommunism, guaranteeing a law-governed state, and 
right-wing economic reform are the main tenets of its program. 
Ivan Duris is RBRS chairman and Imrich Tichy is the party's 
honorary chairman. 

</TEXT>

