<F P=106> [TA SR report: "For the Nuclear Plant's Safety"] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava--"An agreement has been signed between 
the Jaslovske Bohunice nuclear power plant and the Siemens 
Aktiengesellschaft, Berlin und Munich company on the gradual 
reconstruction of the Bohunice nuclear power plant," said J. 
Sidor, press secretary of the Slovak Energy Enterprise, 
Bratislava. He added that, on the basis of this agreement, the 
plant's safety systems will be improved stage by stage, and, 
thus, its equipment will correspond to the normal international 
standard for water-pressure reactors. In this context, the 
older reactors will also be supplied with the necessary 
equipment. 

</TEXT>

